In addition, infected camels excrete the virus not only through the respiratory tract but also through feces, which is also the main route of excretion for bats.
We cannot rule out the possibility that pangolins are one of the intermediate animal hosts of SARS-CoV-2.
In addition, the distance between SARS-CoV-2 and RaTG13 is even less than that separating SARS-CoV-2 and SARS-CoV-2-associated beta-CoVs from pangolins.
